======================================================================
                  Standardized test collection
======================================================================

Here is a collection of standard tests with the
corresponding reference output and necessary input files.


The format for the filenames are

XML FILES (mandatory)
---------------------
(executable).(short test name).xml

REFERENCE FILES (mandatory)
---------------------------
(executable).(short test name).reference.(generating architecture)

INPUT FILES (if necessary)
--------------------------
here any input file necessary for reproducing the Reference Files.
Some examples are
(executable).(short test name).conf
(executable).(short test name).seed
(executable).(short test name).input

In general
(executable).(short test name).(type of input)


->->->->->->->->->
     EXAMPLE
->->->->->->->->->

For a test named "my_test" using "test_exe" as executable and 
tested on a INTEL machine, single core

- test_exe.my_test.xml
- test_exe.my_test.input
- test_exe.my_test.reference.INTEL_1core


nununununununununununununununununununununununununununununununnunununun
               Tests brief explanation
nununununununununununununununununununununununununununununununnunununun

-- gauge_std_test
Simple Symanzik gauge action starting from Unit configuration
Tests just the HMC and Gauge routines

-- 2+1_rect_DWF_Hasenbusch
2+1 flavors of Domain Wall fermions using Hasenbusch preconditioning
Tests pretty much all RHMC relevant routines



